Musk was criticized for his public comments and conduct related to the COVID-19 pandemic.[357][358] He spread misinformation about the virus, including promoting a widely discredited paper on the benefits of chloroquine and a study that suggested doctors inflated COVID-19 case numbers for financial gain.[359][360][361]

In March 2020, Musk stated, "The coronavirus panic is dumb."[362][363] In an email to Tesla employees, Musk referred to COVID-19 as a "specific form of the common cold" and predicted that confirmed COVID-19 cases would not exceed 0.1% of the US population.[364][357] On March 19, 2020, Musk predicted that there would be "probably close to zero new cases in [the US] by end of April".[358][365] Politico labeled this statement one of "the most audacious, confident and spectacularly incorrect prognostications [of 2020]".[366] Musk also claimed falsely that children "are essentially immune" to COVID-19.[367][368]

Musk repeatedly condemned COVID-19 lockdowns and refused to close the Tesla Fremont factory in March 2020, defying the local shelter-in-place order.[357][369][370][371] In May 2020, he reopened the Tesla factory, defying the local stay-at-home order,[372][373] and warned workers that they would be unpaid and their pandemic unemployment benefits might be jeopardized if they did not report to work.[373]

In March 2020, Musk promised that Tesla would make ventilators for COVID-19 patients if there was a shortage.[374] After figures like New York City mayor Bill de Blasio responded to Musk's offer,[375] Musk said he thought the ventilators which Tesla was working on would probably be unneeded.[376] Later, Musk offered to donate ventilators which Tesla would build or buy from a third party.[374] However, instead of the much more expensive and sought-after invasive mechanical ventilator (IMV) machines, Musk eventually bought and donated medical devices that hospitals noted were BiPAP and CPAP machines.[377][378][379]

In September 2020, Musk stated that he would not get the COVID-19 vaccine, because he and his children were "not at risk for COVID".[380][381][382] Two months later, Musk contracted COVID-19 and suggested his COVID-19 rapid antigen test results were dubious, after which the phrase "Space Karen" trended on Twitter, in reference to Musk.[383][384][361] However, in December 2021, Musk revealed that he and his eligible children had received the vaccine.[385]

Finance
Musk has stated that he does not believe the US government should provide subsidies to companies; instead they should use a carbon tax to discourage poor behavior.[386][387] Musk says that the free market would achieve the best solution, and that producing environmentally unfriendly vehicles should come with its own consequences.[388] His stance has been called hypocritical as Tesla has received billions of dollars in subsidies.[389][390] In addition, Tesla made large sums from government-initiated systems of zero emissions credits offered in California and the United States federal level, which enabled improved initial consumer adoption of Tesla vehicles, as the tax credits given by governments enabled Tesla's battery electric vehicles to be price-competitive, in relative comparison with existing lower-priced internal combustion engine vehicles.[391] Notably, Tesla generates a sizeable portion of its revenue from its sales of carbon credits granted to the company, by both the European Union Emissions Trading System and the Chinese national carbon trading scheme.[392][393][394][395]

Musk, a longtime opponent of short-selling, has repeatedly criticized the practice and argued it should be illegal.[396][397] Musk's opposition to short-selling has been speculated to stem from how short-sellers often organize and publish opposition research about the companies that they believe are currently overvalued.[398] In early 2021, he encouraged the GameStop short squeeze.[399][400]

Cryptocurrency
Musk has promoted cryptocurrencies, stating that he supports them over traditional government-issued fiat currencies.[401] Given the influence of Musk's tweets on moving cryptocurrency markets,[402] his statements around cryptocurrencies have been viewed as market manipulations by some, such as the critic Nouriel Roubini.[403] Musk's social media praising of Bitcoin and Dogecoin was credited for increasing their prices. Consequently, Tesla's 2021 announcement that it bought $1.5 billion worth of Bitcoin raised questions against the backdrop of Musk's social media behavior.[404] Tesla's announcement that it would accept Bitcoin for payment was criticized by environmentalists and investors due to the environmental impact of cryptocurrency mining; in 2021, the energy consumption of Bitcoin mining, which has built-in energy inefficiency, exceeded that of Argentina. A few months later, in response to the criticism, Musk announced on Twitter that Tesla would no longer accept Bitcoin and would not engage in any Bitcoin transactions until the environmental issues are solved.[405][406]

Personal life
From the early 2000s until late 2020, Musk resided in California where both Tesla and SpaceX were founded and where their headquarters are still located.[407] In 2020, he moved to Texas, stating that California had become "complacent" with its economic success.[407][408]

While hosting Saturday Night Live in May 2021, Musk stated that he has Asperger syndrome.[409] The BBC wrote, "It is thought to be the first time Mr Musk has spoken about his condition."[410]

Marriages, dating life, and children
Musk met his first wife, Canadian Justine Wilson, while attending Queen's University, and they married in 2000.[411] He contracted malaria in 2000 while on vacation in South Africa, and nearly died.[412] In 2002, their first child died of sudden infant death syndrome (SIDS) at the age of 10 weeks.[413] After his death, the couple decided to use IVF to continue their family.[414] They had twins in 2004 followed by triplets in 2006.[414] Musk and Wilson divorced in 2008 and shared custody of their children.[411][415][416] One of their children, who is a trans woman, filed a request in April 2022 for a name change to reflect her gender identity and because she no longer wished to be associated with Musk.[417]

In 2008, Musk began dating English actor Talulah Riley.[418] They married in September 2010 at Dornoch Cathedral in Scotland.[419][420] In 2012, he announced a divorce from Riley.[421][422] In 2013, Musk and Riley remarried. In December 2014, he filed for a second divorce from Riley; however, the action was withdrawn.[423] A second divorce was finalized in 2016.[424] Musk then dated Amber Heard for several months in 2017;[425][426] he had reportedly been pursuing her since 2012.[426] Musk was later accused by Johnny Depp of having an affair with Heard while she was still married to Depp.[427][428][429] Musk and Heard both denied the affair.[427]

In 2018, Musk and Canadian musician Grimes revealed that they were dating.[430][431][432] Grimes gave birth to their son in May 2020.[433][434] According to Musk and Grimes, his name was "X Æ A-12"; however, the name would have violated California regulations as it contained characters that are not in the modern English alphabet,[435][436] and was then changed to "X Æ A-Xii". This drew more confusion, as Æ is not a letter in the modern English alphabet.[437] The child was eventually named "X AE A-XII" Musk, with "X" as a first name, "AE A-XII" as a middle name, and "Musk" as surname.[438] Musk confirmed reports that the couple are "semi-separated" in September 2021; in an interview with Time in December 2021, he said he was single.[439][440][441] In March 2022, Grimes said of her relationship with Musk: "I would probably refer to him as my boyfriend, but we're very fluid." She further revealed that their first daughter, nicknamed Y, was born in December 2021 via surrogate.[2] Later that month, Grimes tweeted that she and Musk had broken up again "but he's my best friend and the love of my life."[442]

Sexual misconduct allegation
In May 2022, a Business Insider article alleged that Musk engaged in sexual misconduct with a SpaceX flight attendant in a private jet in 2016. According to the article, citing an anonymous friend of a flight attendant, in November 2018, Musk, SpaceX and the former flight attendant entered into a severance agreement granting the attendant a $250,000 payment in exchange for a promise not to sue over the claims.[443]

Musk stated, "If I were inclined to engage in sexual harassment, this is unlikely to be the first time in my entire 30-year career that it comes to light". Musk accused the article from Business Insider of being a "politically motivated hit piece".[444][445] He also suggested that the scandal should be known as "Elongate".[446][undue weight? – discuss]

After the release of the Business Insider article, Tesla's stock fell by more than 6%,[447] decreasing Musk's net worth by $10 billion.[448] The financial newspaper Barron's wrote "...some investors considered key-man risk - the danger that a company could be badly hurt by the loss of one individual."[449]

Public recognition
In popular culture
Musk has made multiple cameos and appearances in films such as Iron Man 2 (2010),[450] Machete Kills (2013),[451] Why Him? (2016),[452] and Men in Black: International (2019).[453] Television series on which he has appeared include The Simpsons ("The Musk Who Fell to Earth", 2015),[454] The Big Bang Theory ("The Platonic Permutation", 2015),[455] South Park ("Members Only", 2016),[456][457] Rick and Morty ("One Crew over the Crewcoo's Morty", 2019),[458][459] Young Sheldon ("A Patch, a Modem, and a Zantac®", 2017)[460] and Saturday Night Live (2021).[461] He has contributed interviews to the documentaries Racing Extinction (2015) and the Werner Herzog-directed Lo and Behold (2016).[462][463]

In China, Musk has become a "trademark phenomenon" according to SCMP, with over 270 different companies having registered trademarks using his English name or Chinese transliteration, for a multitude of products including printing, restaurants, textiles, and design.[464]

Accolades
Main article: List of awards and honors received by Elon Musk
Musk was elected a fellow of the Royal Society (FRS) in 2018.[465] In 2015 he received an honorary doctorate in engineering and technology at Yale[466] and IEEE Honorary Membership.[467] Awards for his contributions to the development of the Falcon rockets include the American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics George Low Transportation Award in 2008,[468] the Fédération Aéronautique Internationale Gold Space Medal in 2010,[469] and the Royal Aeronautical Society Gold Medal in 2012.[470] He was listed among Time magazine's 100 Most Influential People in 2010,[471] 2013,[472] 2018,[473] and 2021.[474] Musk was selected as Time's "Person of the Year" for 2021. Time editor-in-chief Edward Felsenthal wrote that "Person of the Year is a marker of influence, and few individuals have had more influence than Musk on life on Earth, and potentially life off Earth too".[475][476] In 2022, Musk was elected as a member into the National Academy of Engineering.[477]

